Class ExpressionTree

java.lang.Object
  aesi.ExpressionTree
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public final class ExpressionTree
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable

A tree that recursively represents expressions (needs more documentation). Changing, adding and removing nodes or leafs is done by travelling down the tree to the node or leaf that needs to be changed or removed or added to and performing that operation. All expressions are represented as parts of strings.

getRandomValue

public java.lang.String getRandomValue()
Returns a random value for a leaf. This can be a call, random value (generated by the random number generator) or a private variable. In the future we do want to be able to weightedly randomly chose between these options instead of just randomly as we do now.
